{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880284549,"sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab6940f001UAAvTIVS3a4sZC","messageID":"msg_d7ab687a5001AbBFiNsCOAQBGm","sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n8: \n9: ### Time threshold\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: var SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n13: ```\n14: \n15: Idle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n16: \n17: ### Annotation key\n18: \n19: The reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n20: \n21: - Import: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager`\n22: - Key: `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` = **`\"last-activity-time\"`**\n23: \n24: (Workload manager also sets `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` on Sandbox metadata for template-driven idle configuration; **agentd** only reads `last-activity-time`.)\n25: \n26: ### Reconciler\n27: \n28: ```go\n29: package agentd\n30: \n31: type Reconciler struct {\n32:     client.Client\n33:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n34: }\n35: \n36: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n37: ```\n38: \n39: **Algorithm (exact behavior):**\n40: \n41: 1. `sandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}`; `Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)`.\n42: 2. If `errors.IsNotFound(err)` → `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`.\n43: 3. If other get error → return `ctrl.Result{}, err`.\n44: 4. `lastActivityStr, exists := sandbox.Annotations[workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey]`.\n45: 5. If `exists && lastActivityStr != \"\"`:\n46:    - `lastActivity, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)`\n47:    - If parse err → `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second}, err`\n48:    - `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`\n49:    - If `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`:\n50:      - `r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)`; if err and not `IsNotFound` → `return ctrl.Result{}, err`\n51:    - Else:\n52:      - `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil`\n53: 6. `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n54: \n55: ### SetupWithManager\n56: \n57: ```go\n58: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n59:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n60:         For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n61:         Complete(r)\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## Binary `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n66: \n67: ### Scheme registration\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: var schemeBuilder = runtime.NewScheme()\n71: \n72: func init() {\n73:     utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n74:     utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n75: }\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### Controller-runtime manager\n79: \n80: ```go\n81: mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n82:     Scheme:                 schemeBuilder,\n83:     Metrics:                metricsserver.Options{BindAddress: \"0\"},\n84:     HealthProbeBindAddress:   \"0\",\n85: })\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### Controller registration (duplicate of SetupWithManager pattern)\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: err = ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n92:     For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n93:     Complete(&agentd.Reconciler{\n94:         Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n95:         Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n96:     })\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ### Run\n100: \n101: ```go\n102: mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ## Watched resources\n106: \n107: | API group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n108: |-----------|---------|------|---------|\n109: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Default `For()` watch — creates, updates, deletes (per controller-runtime) |\n110: \n111: No explicit `Owns` or `Watches` — single primary resource `Sandbox`.\n112: \n113: ## Related workload-manager constants (context)\n114: \n115: From `pkg/workloadmanager` (not used by agentd reconcile logic but set when sandboxes are created):\n116: \n117: - `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"` — duration string on Sandbox CR.\n118: - `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"` — **read by agentd** for idle cleanup.\n119: \n120: ## Dependencies\n121: \n122: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors`\n123: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime`\n124: - `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`\n125: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`\n126: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` (annotation key only)\n\n(End of file - total 126 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup — Design\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n\n### Time threshold\n\n```go\nvar SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n```\n\nIdle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n\n### Annotation key\n\nThe reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md","time":{"start":1775880284513,"end":1775880284547}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880284551,"sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab69abc001JweLZzy2bo1SOf","messageID":"msg_d7ab687a5001AbBFiNsCOAQBGm","sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Run a controller that deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when an idle-timeout annotation indicates the sandbox has been inactive beyond a fixed grace period.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Reconciliation trigger\n9: The system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager’s API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n12: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n13: - **WHEN** the manager is running\n14: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object’s namespace and name\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Idle detection input\n17: The system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n20: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` without `last-activity-time`\n21: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n22: - **THEN** the sandbox is not deleted and result has zero `RequeueAfter`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Idle detection parsing\n25: When the annotation is non-empty, the system SHALL parse it with `time.RFC3339`. On parse error, the system SHALL return `RequeueAfter: 30 seconds` and the parse error.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Invalid timestamp requeues\n28: - **GIVEN** annotation value is not RFC3339\n29: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n30: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Expiration threshold\n33: The system SHALL define `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`. The system SHALL compute `expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`. When `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`, the system SHALL delete the `Sandbox` resource.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Idle beyond 15 minutes triggers delete\n36: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to a time more than 15 minutes in the past\n37: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n38: - **THEN** the controller calls delete on the `Sandbox` client object\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Not yet expired requeues until expiration\n41: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is recent enough that expiration is in the future\n42: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n43: - **THEN** the result is `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)` and no delete occurs\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: Delete idempotency\n46: When delete returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL treat it as success and SHALL return empty result with nil error. Other delete errors SHALL be returned to trigger retry.\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Already deleted sandbox\n49: - **GIVEN** the API server returns not found on delete\n50: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n51: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Get not found\n54: When get returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL return empty result and nil error.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Sandbox removed before reconcile\n57: - **GIVEN** the sandbox no longer exists\n58: - **WHEN** `Get` fails with not found\n59: - **THEN** reconcile returns without error\n60: \n61: ## Requirements (binary / operator)\n62: \n63: ### Requirement: Manager options\n64: The `agentd` binary SHALL construct controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1` from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`, SHALL disable metrics server (`BindAddress: \"0\"`), and SHALL disable health probe server (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`).\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Signal-driven shutdown\n67: - **GIVEN** the process runs `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())`\n68: - **WHEN** SIGTERM/SIGINT is received\n69: - **THEN** the manager stops gracefully per controller-runtime defaults\n\n(End of file - total 69 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup Specification\n\n## Purpose\nRun a controller that deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when an idle-timeout annotation indicates the sandbox has been inactive beyond a fixed grace period.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciliation trigger\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager’s API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n- **WHEN** the manager is running\n- **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object’s namespace and name\n\n### Requirement: Idle detection input\nThe system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n\n#### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` without `last-activity-time`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md","time":{"start":1775880284520,"end":1775880284550}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880284554,"sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab6a432001H7OMs7E84Ees2J","messageID":"msg_d7ab687a5001AbBFiNsCOAQBGm","sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 (PicoD JWT Middleware)\n2: \n3: > **Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n4: > **Language:** Go  \n5: > **Size:** S  \n6: > **Stage:** ST-1 (Kickoff) → ST-2 (Design)  \n7: > **Base Spec:** AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API)\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: AR-017 implements JWT authentication middleware for PicoD API endpoints. The middleware validates bearer tokens using HMAC (HS256) or RSA (RS256) signatures, with support for expiration and issuer claim validation.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## ST-2.1 — Type Definitions\n18: \n19: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n20: |---|------|--------------|------|\n21: | 2.1.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n22: | 2.1.2 | Define `Claims` struct (Subject, Issuer, ExpiresAt, IssuedAt) | All fields present with JSON tags | 0.5h |\n23: | 2.1.3 | Define `ValidationOptions` struct | Algorithm, Secret/PublicKey, ExpectedIssuer, ClockSkew fields | 0.5h |\n24: | 2.1.4 | Define `MiddlewareOptions` struct | Validator and ErrorHandler fields | 0.5h |\n25: \n26: **Deliverable:** Type definitions compile and match delta-spec.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## ST-2.2 — Error Definitions\n31: \n32: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n33: |---|------|--------------|------|\n34: | 2.2.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n35: | 2.2.2 | Define `ErrMissingToken` | Error message defined | 0.25h |\n36: | 2.2.3 | Define `ErrInvalidTokenFormat` | Error message defined | 0.25h |\n37: | 2.2.4 | Define `ErrInvalidSignature` | Error message defined | 0.25h |\n38: | 2.2.5 | Define `ErrTokenExpired` | Error message defined | 0.25h |\n39: | 2.2.6 | Define `ErrInvalidIssuer` | Error message defined | 0.25h |\n40: | 2.2.7 | Define `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm` | Error message defined | 0.25h |\n41: \n42: **Deliverable:** All error types defined and exportable.\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## ST-2.3 — Token Validation\n47: \n48: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n49: |---|------|--------------|------|\n50: | 2.3.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n51: | 2.3.2 | Define `JWTValidator` interface with ValidateToken method | Interface signature matches spec | 0.5h |\n52: | 2.3.3 | Implement `NewValidator(opts ValidationOptions) (JWTValidator, error)` | Returns initialized validator | 0.5h |\n53: | 2.3.4 | Implement HS256 signature verification | Valid token passes, invalid fails | 1h |\n54: | 2.3.5 | Implement RS256 signature verification | Valid token passes, invalid fails | 1h |\n55: | 2.3.6 | Implement token parsing with claims extraction | Claims extracted correctly | 0.5h |\n56: | 2.3.7 | Implement expiration validation with clock skew | Expired tokens rejected, skew applied | 0.5h |\n57: | 2.3.8 | Implement issuer claim validation | Wrong issuer returns error | 0.5h |\n58: | 2.3.9 | Implement algorithm validation | Unsupported alg rejected | 0.5h |\n59: \n60: **Deliverable:** Validator implementation with all algorithms.\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## ST-2.4 — HTTP Middleware\n65: \n66: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n67: |---|------|--------------|------|\n68: | 2.4.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n69: | 2.4.2 | Implement `JWTMiddleware(opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler` | Returns middleware function | 0.5h |\n70: | 2.4.3 | Implement bearer token extraction from Authorization header | Token extracted correctly | 0.5h |\n71: | 2.4.4 | Implement error handling with standardized responses | JSON error responses match spec | 0.5h |\n72: | 2.4.5 | Implement claims injection into request context | GetClaims retrieves claims | 0.5h |\n73: | 2.4.6 | Implement `GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)` helper | Returns claims if present | 0.5h |\n74: \n75: **Deliverable:** Middleware function that validates tokens on HTTP requests.\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## ST-2.5 — Configuration\n80: \n81: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n82: |---|------|--------------|------|\n83: | 2.5.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n84: | 2.5.2 | Implement `LoadConfigFromEnv() (*ValidationOptions, error)` | Reads all env vars | 0.5h |\n85: | 2.5.3 | Support PICOD_JWT_SECRET for HS256 | Secret loaded correctly | 0.5h |\n86: | 2.5.4 | Support PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY for RS256 | Key file loaded and parsed | 0.5h |\n87: | 2.5.5 | Support PICOD_JWT_ISSUER (required) | Error if missing | 0.5h |\n88: | 2.5.6 | Support PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW parsing | Duration parsed correctly | 0.5h |\n89: | 2.5.7 | Support PICOD_JWT_ALG selection | Algorithm selected correctly | 0.5h |\n90: \n91: **Deliverable:** Configuration loading from environment.\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## ST-2.6 — Unit Tests (Validator)\n96: \n97: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n98: |---|------|--------------|------|\n99: | 2.6.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | File compiles with build tag | 0.5h |\n100: | 2.6.2 | Write `TestValidateToken_HS256_Success` | Valid token passes | 0.5h |\n101: | 2.6.3 | Write `TestValidateToken_HS256_InvalidSignature` | Wrong secret fails | 0.5h |\n102: | 2.6.4 | Write `TestValidateToken_RS256_Success` | Valid RSA token passes | 0.5h |\n103: | 2.6.5 | Write `TestValidateToken_RS256_InvalidSignature` | Wrong key fails | 0.5h |\n104: | 2.6.6 | Write `TestValidateToken_Expired` | Expired token rejected | 0.5h |\n105: | 2.6.7 | Write `TestValidateToken_ClockSkew` | Skew tolerance applied | 0.5h |\n106: | 2.6.8 | Write `TestValidateToken_InvalidIssuer` | Wrong issuer rejected | 0.5h |\n107: | 2.6.9 | Write `TestValidateToken_UnsupportedAlgorithm` | ES256 rejected if not allowed | 0.5h |\n108: \n109: **Deliverable:** Validator tests pass with >85% coverage.\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## ST-2.7 — Unit Tests (Middleware)\n114: \n115: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n116: |---|------|--------------|------|\n117: | 2.7.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n118: | 2.7.2 | Write `TestMiddleware_ValidToken` | Request with valid token passes to handler | 0.5h |\n119: | 2.7.3 | Write `TestMiddleware_MissingToken` | Returns 401 with correct error | 0.5h |\n120: | 2.7.4 | Write `TestMiddleware_InvalidFormat` | Returns 401 for malformed header | 0.5h |\n121: | 2.7.5 | Write `TestMiddleware_InvalidSignature` | Returns 401 for bad signature | 0.5h |\n122: | 2.7.6 | Write `TestMiddleware_ExpiredToken` | Returns 401 for expired token | 0.5h |\n123: | 2.7.7 | Write `TestMiddleware_InvalidIssuer` | Returns 403 for wrong issuer | 0.5h |\n124: | 2.7.8 | Write `TestMiddleware_ContextPropagation` | Claims available in handler context | 0.5h |\n125: \n126: **Deliverable:** Middleware tests pass.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## ST-2.8 — Integration Tests\n131: \n132: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n133: |---|------|--------------|------|\n134: | 2.8.1 | Create `pkg/picod/jwt/integration_test.go` | File with build tag | 0.5h |\n135: | 2.8.2 | Write `TestIntegration_EndToEnd` | Full middleware flow | 0.5h |\n136: | 2.8.3 | Write test helpers for token generation | Can generate test JWTs | 0.5h |\n137: \n138: **Deliverable:** Integration tests pass.\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## ST-2.9 — Documentation\n143: \n144: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n145: |---|------|--------------|------|\n146: | 2.9.1 | Add package-level GoDoc | Overview documentation | 0.5h |\n147: | 2.9.2 | Document exported types | Clear usage docs | 0.5h |\n148: | 2.9.3 | Document exported functions | Parameters and return values | 0.5h |\n149: | 2.9.4 | Add usage example | Example code in godoc | 0.5h |\n150: \n151: **Deliverable:** Code is well-documented.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## Summary\n156: \n157: | Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n158: |-------|-------|------------|\n159: | ST-2.1: Type Definitions | 4 | 2h |\n160: | ST-2.2: Error Definitions | 7 | 2h |\n161: | ST-2.3: Token Validation | 9 | 5h |\n162: | ST-2.4: HTTP Middleware | 6 | 3h |\n163: | ST-2.5: Configuration | 7 | 3.5h |\n164: | ST-2.6: Unit Tests (Validator) | 9 | 4.5h |\n165: | ST-2.7: Unit Tests (Middleware) | 8 | 4h |\n166: | ST-2.8: Integration Tests | 3 | 1.5h |\n167: | ST-2.9: Documentation | 4 | 2h |\n168: | **Total** | **57** | **27.5h** |\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ## File Deliverables Checklist\n173: \n174: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` — Type definitions\n175: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` — Error definitions\n176: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` — JWTValidator implementation\n177: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` — HTTP middleware\n178: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` — Configuration loading\n179: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` — Validator unit tests\n180: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` — Middleware unit tests\n181: - [ ] `pkg/picod/jwt/integration_test.go` — Integration tests\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## Verification Commands\n186: \n187: ```bash\n188: # Build verification\n189: go build ./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n190: \n191: # Unit tests\n192: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -v\n193: \n194: # With coverage\n195: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -cover\n196: \n197: # Race detection\n198: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -race\n199: \n200: # Integration tests\n201: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -tags=integration -v\n202: ```\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ## Definition of Done\n207: \n208: - [ ] All 57 tasks complete\n209: - [ ] JWTValidator interface fully implemented\n210: - [ ] HTTP middleware validates tokens correctly\n211: - [ ] Unit tests pass (>85% coverage)\n212: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n213: - [ ] Race detector clean\n214: - [ ] `go build ./pkg/picod/jwt/...` succeeds\n215: - [ ] Documentation complete with GoDoc\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## Dependencies\n220: \n221: | Dependency | Purpose |\n222: |------------|---------|\n223: | AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API | Integration target |\n224: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | JWT parsing and validation |\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Design Notes\n229: \n230: - **Algorithm preference**: RS256 for production, HS256 for simpler setups\n231: - **Token source**: HTTP Authorization header only (Bearer scheme)\n232: - **Required claims**: exp (expiration), iss (issuer)\n233: - **Clock skew**: Configurable, default 1 minute\n234: - **Context key**: Private key for claims storage in context\n235: - **Error responses**: JSON format with error/message fields\n\n(End of file - total 235 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 (PicoD JWT Middleware)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** S  \n> **Stage:** ST-1 (Kickoff) → ST-2 (Design)  \n> **Base Spec:** AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-017 implements JWT authentication middleware for PicoD API endpoints. The middleware validates bearer tokens using HMAC (HS256) or RSA (RS256) signatures, with support for expiration and issuer claim validation.\n\n---\n\n## ST-2.1 — Type Definitions\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775880284526,"end":1775880284552}}}}
