{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880307947,"sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab6f13f001Q2Vs0lluCXSwZP","messageID":"msg_d7ab6cb2e001Tx5teL3jQTgXQS","sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_functions.bash:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/","description":"List AR-018 directory"},"output":"total 20\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root  4096 Apr 11 11:55 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 20 root root  4096 Apr 11 11:53 ..\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root 11741 Apr 11 11:55 delta-spec.md\n","metadata":{"output":"total 20\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root  4096 Apr 11 11:55 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 20 root root  4096 Apr 11 11:53 ..\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root 11741 Apr 11 11:55 delta-spec.md\n","exit":0,"description":"List AR-018 directory","truncated":false},"title":"List AR-018 directory","time":{"start":1775880307917,"end":1775880307946}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880307971,"sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab6ff02001coW5ECgccXlpoR","messageID":"msg_d7ab6cb2e001Tx5teL3jQTgXQS","sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n2: \n3: > **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n4: > **Language:** Go  \n5: > **Size:** S  \n6: > **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n7: > **Base Spec:** AR-012 (Store Interface Definition)\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: AR-014 implements a Valkey-backed storage provider for the Store interface defined in AR-012. Valkey is an open-source Redis fork that provides high-performance key-value storage with clustering support. This implementation uses the `valkey-go` client library.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## ST-4.1 — Valkey Store Core Structure\n18: \n19: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n20: |---|------|--------------|------|\n21: | 4.1.1 | Create `pkg/store/valkey.go` with `valkeyStore` struct | File compiles; `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds | 0.5h |\n22: | 4.1.2 | Define `valkeyOptions` struct with `InitAddress []string`, `Password`, `DisableCache`, `ForceSingleClient` | Struct fields align with valkey-go ClientOption | 0.5h |\n23: | 4.1.3 | Implement `newValkeyStore()` constructor | Returns Store interface implementation | 0.5h |\n24: | 4.1.4 | Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` for environment parsing | `VALKEY_ADDR`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`, `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | 0.5h |\n25: | 4.1.5 | Add `sessionKey()` helper method for key construction | Returns `session:{id}` format | 0.25h |\n26: \n27: **Deliverable:** Valkey store structure compiles with proper configuration.\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## ST-4.2 — Valkey Core Store Methods\n32: \n33: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n34: |---|------|--------------|------|\n35: | 4.2.1 | Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` | Returns nil on \"PONG\" response; returns error on failure | 0.5h |\n36: | 4.2.2 | Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` | Returns `ErrNotFound` for missing keys; validates empty sessionID | 1h |\n37: | 4.2.3 | Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` | Uses `DoMulti` atomic operation: SET NX + ZADD expiry + ZADD last_activity | 1h |\n38: | 4.2.4 | Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` | Uses SET XX flag; returns error if key doesn't exist | 0.5h |\n39: | 4.2.5 | Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error` | Uses `DoMulti` atomic: DEL + ZREM expiry + ZREM last_activity | 0.5h |\n40: | 4.2.6 | Implement `Close() error` | Calls `s.cli.Close()`; returns nil | 0.25h |\n41: \n42: **Deliverable:** All core CRUD operations work with Valkey backend.\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## ST-4.3 — Valkey Index Management Methods\n47: \n48: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n49: |---|------|--------------|------|\n50: | 4.3.1 | Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` | Uses `ZRANGEBYSCORE` on `session:expiry`; returns nil if limit <= 0 | 1h |\n51: | 4.3.2 | Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` | Uses `ZRANGEBYSCORE` on `session:last_activity` | 1h |\n52: | 4.3.3 | Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper | Uses `MGET` for batch fetch; skips orphaned entries gracefully | 1h |\n53: | 4.3.4 | Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` | Checks EXISTS first; uses `time.Now()` if at.IsZero() | 0.5h |\n54: \n55: **Deliverable:** Index operations support session lifecycle management.\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## ST-4.4 — Valkey Error Handling\n60: \n61: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n62: |---|------|--------------|------|\n63: | 4.4.1 | Translate `valkey.IsValkeyNil()` to `ErrNotFound` | Unit test: missing key returns `ErrNotFound` | 0.5h |\n64: | 4.4.2 | Handle SET NX failure (session already exists) | Returns \"session already exists\" error | 0.5h |\n65: | 4.4.3 | Handle SET XX failure (key not exists) | Returns \"key not exists\" error | 0.5h |\n66: | 4.4.4 | Handle `DoMulti` partial failures | Returns error from first failed command | 0.5h |\n67: \n68: **Deliverable:** Error handling consistent with Redis implementation.\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## ST-4.5 — Unit Tests — Valkey Implementation\n73: \n74: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n75: |---|------|--------------|------|\n76: | 4.5.1 | Write `TestValkeyStore_Ping` — success and failure | Mock valkey-go client; verify \"PONG\" parsing | 1h |\n77: | 4.5.2 | Write `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID` — validation, not found, success | Verify `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` translation | 1h |\n78: | 4.5.3 | Write `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox` — validation (nil, empty ID, zero ExpiresAt), success, duplicate | Verify atomic `DoMulti` with SET NX + ZADD x2 | 1.5h |\n79: | 4.5.4 | Write `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox` — validation, missing key, success | Verify SET XX behavior | 1h |\n80: | 4.5.5 | Write `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID` — validation, success, idempotent | Verify atomic cleanup of session + indexes | 1h |\n81: | 4.5.6 | Write `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes` — limit <= 0, expired sessions, limit applied | Verify `ZRANGEBYSCORE` + `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` | 1h |\n82: | 4.5.7 | Write `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes` — inactive sessions | Similar to expired tests | 1h |\n83: | 4.5.8 | Write `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity` — validation, not found, zero time, specific time | Verify EXISTS check + ZADD | 1h |\n84: | 4.5.9 | Write `TestValkeyStore_LoadSandboxesBySessionIDs` — empty, orphaned entries, batch load | Verify MGET + orphan skipping | 1h |\n85: | 4.5.10 | Write `TestValkeyStore_Close` — connection release | Verify `cli.Close()` called | 0.5h |\n86: \n87: **Deliverable:** `go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestValkey` passes with >80% coverage.\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## ST-4.6 — Unit Tests — Configuration\n92: \n93: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n94: |---|------|--------------|------|\n95: | 4.6.1 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_MissingAddr` — error when VALKEY_ADDR unset | Returns error | 0.5h |\n96: | 4.6.2 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_PasswordRequired` — error when password required but missing | Returns error | 0.5h |\n97: | 4.6.3 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_PasswordOptional` — success when VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false | Allows empty password | 0.5h |\n98: | 4.6.4 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_MultipleAddresses` — comma-separated VALKEY_ADDR parsing | Splits and trims addresses | 0.5h |\n99: | 4.6.5 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_DisableCache` — parse VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE | Sets DisableCache field | 0.5h |\n100: | 4.6.6 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_ForceSingle` — parse VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE | Sets ForceSingleClient field | 0.5h |\n101: | 4.6.7 | Write `TestNewValkeyStore` — integration with makeValkeyOptions | Returns valid Store interface | 0.5h |\n102: \n103: **Deliverable:** Configuration tests pass with environment variable isolation.\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## ST-4.7 — Integration Tests\n108: \n109: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n110: |---|------|--------------|------|\n111: | 4.7.1 | Create `pkg/store/valkey_integration_test.go` with testcontainers | Setup real Valkey container | 1.5h |\n112: | 4.7.2 | Write end-to-end CRUD test — full lifecycle | Store → Get → Update → Delete | 1h |\n113: | 4.7.3 | Write index consistency test | Verify ZSETs maintained correctly | 1h |\n114: | 4.7.4 | Write concurrent access safety test | 10 concurrent operations, no race | 1h |\n115: | 4.7.5 | Write orphaned entry tolerance test | Delete session data, verify list skips gracefully | 1h |\n116: \n117: **Deliverable:** Integration tests pass with real Valkey instance.\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ## ST-4.8 — Documentation\n122: \n123: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n124: |---|------|--------------|------|\n125: | 4.8.1 | Add package-level GoDoc for valkey.go | `go doc ./pkg/store` shows Valkey implementation | 0.5h |\n126: | 4.8.2 | Document `valkeyStore` struct with inline comments | Clear explanation of fields | 0.5h |\n127: | 4.8.3 | Document each method with purpose and behavior | Godoc format comments | 0.5h |\n128: | 4.8.4 | Add environment variable documentation | List all VALKEY_* variables | 0.5h |\n129: \n130: **Deliverable:** Code is well-documented for future maintainers.\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ## Summary\n135: \n136: | Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n137: |-------|-------|------------|\n138: | ST-4.1: Core Structure | 5 | 2.25h |\n139: | ST-4.2: Core Methods | 6 | 3.75h |\n140: | ST-4.3: Index Management | 4 | 3h |\n141: | ST-4.4: Error Handling | 4 | 2h |\n142: | ST-4.5: Unit Tests (Valkey) | 10 | 10h |\n143: | ST-4.6: Unit Tests (Config) | 7 | 3.5h |\n144: | ST-4.7: Integration Tests | 5 | 5.5h |\n145: | ST-4.8: Documentation | 4 | 2h |\n146: | **Total** | **45** | **32h** |\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## File Deliverables Checklist\n151: \n152: - [ ] `pkg/store/valkey.go` — Valkey Store implementation\n153: - [ ] `pkg/store/valkey_test.go` — Valkey unit tests\n154: - [ ] `pkg/store/valkey_integration_test.go` — Valkey integration tests\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ## Verification Commands\n159: \n160: ```bash\n161: # Build verification\n162: go build ./pkg/store/...\n163: \n164: # Unit test verification (all store tests)\n165: go test ./pkg/store/... -v\n166: \n167: # Valkey-specific tests\n168: go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestValkey -v\n169: \n170: # Configuration tests\n171: go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestMakeValkey -v\n172: \n173: # Race detection\n174: go test ./pkg/store/... -race\n175: \n176: # Coverage report\n177: go test ./pkg/store/... -cover\n178: \n179: # Integration tests (requires Docker)\n180: go test ./pkg/store/... -tags=integration -v\n181: ```\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## Definition of Done\n186: \n187: - [ ] All 45 tasks complete\n188: - [ ] `valkeyStore` implements full `Store` interface\n189: - [ ] Unit tests pass (>80% coverage for valkey.go)\n190: - [ ] Configuration tests pass\n191: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real Valkey\n192: - [ ] Race detector clean\n193: - [ ] `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds\n194: - [ ] Documentation complete with GoDoc\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ## Dependencies\n199: \n200: - AR-012: Store interface definition (`pkg/store/store.go`)\n201: - AR-013: Redis implementation (reference patterns)\n202: - `pkg/common/types` for `SandboxInfo` type\n203: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` v1.0.56\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## Design Notes\n208: \n209: - **Key naming:** Uses `session:{id}` prefix consistently\n210: - **Index keys:** `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity` (sorted sets)\n211: - **Atomic operations:** Uses `DoMulti` for multi-command atomicity\n212: - **Orphan tolerance:** List operations skip missing keys without failing\n213: - **Error translation:** `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` → `ErrNotFound`\n214: - **Configuration:** Follows same pattern as Redis with VALKEY_* env vars\n\n(End of file - total 214 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** S  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n> **Base Spec:** AR-012 (Store Interface Definition)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-014 implements a Valkey-backed storage provider for the Store interface defined in AR-012. Valkey is an open-source Redis fork that provides high-performance key-value storage with clustering support. This implementation uses the `valkey-go` client library.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — Valkey Store Core Structure\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775880307927,"end":1775880307960}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775880307996,"sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab705020014dvOYAgqw7fnoI","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7ab6cb2e001Tx5teL3jQTgXQS","sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":29845,"input":4,"output":226,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":1727,"read":27888}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775880316123,"sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab724da001OryNPkv4NFAyz2","messageID":"msg_d7ab705310015jSCH0NllaZBk2","sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880318240,"sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab7282a001ZQionOIRgVqarF","messageID":"msg_d7ab705310015jSCH0NllaZBk2","sessionID":"ses_285499d3bffeOS6QnxS0CK1eWh","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-018\n6: **Module:** `pkg/agentd`\n7: **Language:** Go\n8: **Size:** S\n9: **Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md)\n10: \n11: The Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). It uses the controller-runtime framework for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Reconciliation Trigger\n18: \n19: The system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager's API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n22: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n23: - **AND** the agentd manager is running\n24: - **WHEN** the controller-runtime detects the change\n25: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function SHALL be invoked with the object's namespace and name\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Sandbox deletion triggers reconcile\n28: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is deleted from the cluster\n29: - **AND** the agentd manager is running\n30: - **WHEN** the controller-runtime detects the deletion\n31: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function SHALL be invoked to handle cleanup\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ### Requirement: Idle Detection Input\n36: \n37: The system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue.\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n40: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` exists without the `last-activity-time` annotation\n41: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n42: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL NOT be deleted\n43: - **AND** the result SHALL have zero `RequeueAfter`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Empty annotation value means no deletion\n46: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` exists with `last-activity-time` annotation set to empty string\n47: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n48: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL NOT be deleted\n49: - **AND** the result SHALL have zero `RequeueAfter`\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Idle Detection Parsing\n54: \n55: When the annotation is non-empty, the system SHALL parse it with `time.RFC3339`. On parse error, the system SHALL return `RequeueAfter: 30 seconds` and the parse error.\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Valid RFC3339 timestamp parses successfully\n58: - **GIVEN** annotation value is a valid RFC3339 timestamp (e.g., \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\")\n59: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` is called\n60: - **THEN** the timestamp SHALL be parsed successfully\n61: - **AND** reconciliation SHALL proceed to expiration check\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: Invalid timestamp requeues with error\n64: - **GIVEN** annotation value is not a valid RFC3339 timestamp (e.g., \"invalid-time\")\n65: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n66: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n67: - **AND** the error SHALL be logged\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Malformed timestamp requeues\n70: - **GIVEN** annotation value is malformed (e.g., \"2024-13-45T99:99:99Z\")\n71: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n72: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ### Requirement: Expiration Threshold\n77: \n78: The system SHALL define `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`. The system SHALL compute `expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`. When `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`, the system SHALL delete the `Sandbox` resource.\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Idle beyond 15 minutes triggers delete\n81: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to a time more than 15 minutes in the past\n82: - **AND** `expirationTime = lastActivity + 15 minutes`\n83: - **AND** `time.Now()` is after `expirationTime`\n84: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n85: - **THEN** the controller SHALL call delete on the `Sandbox` resource\n86: - **AND** on success, reconcile SHALL return empty result with nil error\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Not yet expired requeues until expiration\n89: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is recent enough that expiration is in the future\n90: - **AND** `expirationTime = lastActivity + 15 minutes`\n91: - **AND** `time.Now()` is before `expirationTime`\n92: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n93: - **THEN** the result SHALL be `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)`\n94: - **AND** no delete SHALL occur\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Exactly at expiration triggers delete\n97: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is exactly 15 minutes ago\n98: - **AND** `time.Now()` equals `expirationTime`\n99: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n100: - **THEN** the controller SHALL call delete on the `Sandbox` resource\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Delete Idempotency\n105: \n106: When delete returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL treat it as success and SHALL return empty result with nil error. Other delete errors SHALL be returned to trigger retry.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Already deleted sandbox handled gracefully\n109: - **GIVEN** the API server returns `NotFound` on delete\n110: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n111: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n112: - **AND** no error SHALL be logged\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Delete conflict returns error for retry\n115: - **GIVEN** the API server returns a conflict error on delete\n116: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n117: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, err)`\n118: - **AND** controller-runtime SHALL retry with backoff\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Delete network error returns error for retry\n121: - **GIVEN** the API server returns a connection error on delete\n122: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n123: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, err)`\n124: - **AND** controller-runtime SHALL retry with backoff\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ### Requirement: Get Not Found Handling\n129: \n130: When get returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL return empty result and nil error.\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Sandbox removed before reconcile\n133: - **GIVEN** the sandbox no longer exists when Get is called\n134: - **AND** the API server returns `NotFound`\n135: - **WHEN** `Get` fails with not found\n136: - **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` without error\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ### Requirement: Manager Configuration\n141: \n142: The `agentd` binary SHALL construct controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1` from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`, SHALL disable metrics server (`BindAddress: \"0\"`), and SHALL disable health probe server (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`).\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Manager starts with correct configuration\n145: - **GIVEN** the scheme contains core Kubernetes types\n146: - **AND** the scheme contains `sandboxv1alpha1` types\n147: - **AND** metrics server is disabled\n148: - **AND** health probe server is disabled\n149: - **WHEN** the manager is created\n150: - **THEN** the manager SHALL start without error\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Signal-driven shutdown\n153: - **GIVEN** the process runs `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())`\n154: - **WHEN** SIGTERM or SIGINT is received\n155: - **THEN** the manager SHALL stop gracefully per controller-runtime defaults\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ## Changes to Base Specification\n160: \n161: This AR implements the Agentd idle cleanup controller using the client-go library interfaces defined in deployment/client-go.md. No modifications to existing interfaces.\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## New Interfaces\n166: \n167: ### Reconciler Interface\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: package agentd\n171: \n172: import (\n173:     \"context\"\n174:     \"time\"\n175: \n176:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n177:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n178:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/controller/controllerutil\"\n179:     ctrl \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n180: )\n181: \n182: // SessionExpirationTimeout defines the idle timeout before sandbox deletion\n183: var SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n184: \n185: // Reconciler reconciles Sandbox objects for idle cleanup\n186: type Reconciler struct {\n187:     client.Client\n188:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n189: }\n190: \n191: // Reconcile implements the idle cleanup logic\n192: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n193: \n194: // SetupWithManager sets up the controller with the Manager\n195: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### Main Entry Point\n199: \n200: ```go\n201: // cmd/agentd/main.go\n202: \n203: // Scheme registration\n204: var schemeBuilder = runtime.NewSchemeBuilder()\n205: \n206: func init() {\n207:     utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n208:     utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n209: }\n210: \n211: // main creates and runs the controller-runtime manager\n212: func main()\n213: ```\n214: \n215: ---\n216: \n217: ## Modified Interfaces\n218: \n219: None. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n220: \n221: ---\n222: \n223: ## Behavioral Changes\n224: \n225: | Behavior | Before | After |\n226: |----------|--------|-------|\n227: | Sandbox lifecycle | No automatic cleanup | Automatic deletion after 15 min idle |\n228: | Resource tracking | No activity tracking | last-activity-time annotation read |\n229: | Reconciliation | N/A | Controller-runtime reconciler watches Sandboxes |\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ## Dependencies\n234: \n235: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n236: |------------|---------|---------|\n237: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.x | Controller-runtime framework |\n238: | `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1` | Local | Sandbox CRD types |\n239: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | v0.x | Kubernetes API errors |\n240: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | v0.x | Kubernetes runtime types |\n241: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` | Local | Annotation key constants |\n242: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated client (base spec) |\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ## File Index\n247: \n248: | Path | Purpose |\n249: |------|---------|\n250: | `pkg/agentd/reconciler.go` | Reconciler implementation with idle cleanup logic |\n251: | `pkg/agentd/reconciler_test.go` | Unit tests for reconciler |\n252: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Binary entry point and manager setup |\n253: \n254: ---\n255: \n256: ## Constants\n257: \n258: | Constant | Value | Description |\n259: |----------|-------|-------------|\n260: | `SessionExpirationTimeout` | `15 * time.Minute` | Idle timeout before sandbox deletion |\n261: | `RequeueAfterParseError` | `30 * time.Second` | Requeue delay when timestamp parse fails |\n262: \n263: ---\n264: \n265: ## Configuration\n266: \n267: ### Environment Variables\n268: \n269: None. The controller uses hardcoded constants for configuration.\n270: \n271: ### Annotations Read\n272: \n273: | Annotation Key | Source | Description |\n274: |---------------|--------|-------------|\n275: | `last-activity-time` | `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` | RFC3339 timestamp of last sandbox activity |\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## API Endpoints Summary\n280: \n281: This AR is a controller (reconciler) that watches Kubernetes resources; no new API endpoints are exposed.\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ## Watched Resources\n286: \n287: | API Group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n288: |-----------|---------|------|---------|\n289: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Create, Update, Delete |\n290: \n291: No explicit `Owns` or `Watches` — single primary resource `Sandbox`.\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ## Migration Notes\n296: \n297: - Ensure `sandboxv1alpha1` scheme is registered before starting the manager\n298: - The workload manager must set `last-activity-time` annotation on Sandboxes for cleanup to function\n299: - Existing Sandboxes without the annotation will not be cleaned up\n300: - Deploy agentd binary alongside other agentcube components\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n305: \n306: 1. **Reconciliation**: Controller-runtime reconciler registered for Sandbox resources\n307: 2. **Annotation Reading**: Correctly reads `last-activity-time` annotation from Sandbox metadata\n308: 3. **Timestamp Parsing**: Parses RFC3339 timestamps; handles parse errors with 30s requeue\n309: 4. **Expiration Logic**: Correctly computes expiration time (lastActivity + 15 minutes)\n310: 5. **Idle Detection**: Deletes sandboxes idle for more than 15 minutes\n311: 6. **Future Requeue**: Requeues with appropriate delay when expiration is in the future\n312: 7. **Idempotency**: Handles NotFound errors gracefully (no error returned)\n313: 8. **Error Handling**: Returns errors for retry on transient failures\n314: 9. **Manager Setup**: Correctly configures controller-runtime manager with scheme\n315: 10. **Signal Handling**: Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n316: 11. **Unit Tests**: >85% coverage on reconciler logic\n\n(End of file - total 316 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-018\n**Module:** `pkg/agentd`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** S\n**Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md)\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). It uses the controller-runtime framework for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciliation Trigger\n\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager's API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775880318225,"end":1775880318236}}}}
